FBIS4-35269 "drnes104_n_94004" FBIS-NES-94-104 Daily Report 27 May 1994 LEBANON Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping Hizballah Vows Retribution for Kidnapping `Source' Dismisses UN Mediation NC2705184094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 27 May 94 NC2705184094 Beirut Radio Lebanon Arabic BFN [Text] Responding to UN Secretary General Dr. Butrus-Ghali's announcement of his readiness to mediate in the Mustafa al-Dirani issue, a responsible Hizballah source emphasized that Butrus-Ghali's move is aimed at imparting legitimacy to the terrorist Zionist action. The source said the move also proves that the United Nations is no longer an authority fit to make decisions on various issues and conflicts and that it has turned into a podium for the U.S. political stand.
